This section concerns the study of the amplification effect via WM and the quantum correlations shared by the qubits. The amplification effect in the AAV model appears when the denominator in the weak value tends to zero, i.e. when the pre- and post-selected states are almost orthogonal. Hence, as a simple and illustrative example let us consider the case of the two qubits initially prepared in a Bell state, e.g., \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
